<description>Pioneering surgeon Susan Lim performed the first liver transplant in Asia. But a moral concern with transplants led her to look further, and to ask: Could we be transplanting cells, not whole organs? At the INK Conference, she talks through her new research, discovering healing cells in some surprising places.</description>
