<description>On any given day we're lied to from 10 to 200 times, and the clues to detect those lie can be subtle and counter-intuitive. Pamela Meyer, author of &lt;em&gt;Liespotting,&lt;/em&gt; shows the manners and "hotspots" used by those trained to recognize deception -- and she argues honesty is a value worth preserving.</description>
